talk about this properly.

16:11.440 --> 16:13.440
Do we?

16:19.000 --> 16:21.000
What's the point?

16:21.520 --> 16:24.200
You're just gonna tell me
all the ways that I'm wrong.

16:28.640 --> 16:30.260
(SIGHS)

16:30.360 --> 16:35.100
JACK RIVER: ♪ To be by your side

16:35.200 --> 16:38.240
♪ She's walking up to you

16:41.080 --> 16:43.620
♪ She's dying to be... ♪

16:43.720 --> 16:44.900
-(MUSIC STOPS)
-(SINGS) ♪ B... ♪

16:45.000 --> 16:46.180
What's going on?

16:46.280 --> 16:48.540
I need to keep my cortisol
levels low for the baby,

16:48.640 --> 16:52.820
so I'm just releasing some
dopamine into my bloodstream.

16:52.920 --> 16:54.820
Fair. Fair.

16:54.920 --> 16:57.940
Um, can I talk to you
for a second?

16:58.040 --> 16:59.620
-Yeah.
-Is Talia here?

16:59.720 --> 17:01.720
Talia, are you here as well?

17:04.840 --> 17:06.780
What's up?

17:06.880 --> 17:10.620
Um, well, I thought
it would be a good idea

17:10.720 --> 17:12.820
if us three have a low-key chat
about everything.

17:12.920 --> 17:14.180
Good idea.

17:14.280 --> 17:15.780
-Sure thing.
-Cool.

17:15.880 --> 17:17.420
Um, I didn't really think
about it before,

17:17.520 --> 17:20.420
but what we're doing is epic.

17:20.520 --> 17:23.580
Yeah. It is.

17:23.680 --> 17:25.420
It's huge.

17:25.520 --> 17:27.020
It's really cool.

17:27.120 --> 17:28.900
Um... (CLEARS THROAT)

17:29.000 --> 17:32.060
But whether we want them to
or not,

17:32.160 --> 17:34.140
thing are going to change.

17:34.240 --> 17:36.380
-So, firstly...
-I'm not going back to work.

17:36.480 --> 17:37.860
Oh, my God.

17:37.960 --> 17:40.180
It makes me unhappy, Talia,
and that makes the baby unhappy.

17:40.280 --> 17:41.860
-Is that what you want?
-Of course not.

17:41.960 --> 17:43.460
But we all have to
make compromises.

17:43.560 --> 17:45.980
-No, not about this, we don't.
-Yes, we do.

17:46.080 --> 17:47.220
OK, can we take a...

17:47.320 --> 17:49.820
ARIEL: I am not
going to apologise

17:49.920 --> 17:51.300
for wanting the best
for my child.

17:51.400 --> 17:53.300
-YOUR child?
-Hey, OK.

17:53.400 --> 17:55.700
Look, this is what I mean.
This is exactly what I mean.

17:55.800 --> 17:57.180
-Everyone has their concerns.
-No, no.

17:57.280 --> 17:58.620
We are in this together, Ariel.

17:58.720 --> 18:00.300
You don't get to make
unilateral decisions.

18:00.400 --> 18:02.940
-Stop talking to me like that!
-Like what? Truthfully?

18:03.040 --> 18:05.060
No, zzzz, aggressively.

18:05.160 --> 18:06.540
-OK.
-Wow!

18:06.640 --> 18:08.380
OK, can we keep
everything chill?

18:08.480 --> 18:10.340
You know that
I can't get stressed out

18:10.440 --> 18:13.420
and you are deliberately
stressing me out!

18:13.520 --> 18:15.620
Cool. Hey, how about
I never speak to you again?

18:15.720 --> 18:17.700
Do you know what?
That would actually be great.

18:17.800 --> 18:19.840
-Fine.
-Fine.

18:25.800 --> 18:28.920
JACK RIVER: ♪ Be by your side

18:30.200 --> 18:31.940
♪ Fool's gold... ♪

18:32.040 --> 18:34.380
-(LIVELY CHATTER)
-SANTI: Hello, puchita!

18:34.480 --> 18:36.620
-BERNADITA: Ohh.
-SANTI: Mmm.

18:36.720 --> 18:39.500
-Beautiful.
-Do you wanna say hi to Ita?

18:39.600 --> 18:41.600
BERNADITA: Hello, beautiful.

18:42.680 --> 18:43.940
Hello.

18:44.040 --> 18:45.940
Hey, do you want to go play
there with Maddie?

18:46.040 --> 18:47.820
(GASPS) Yeah!

18:47.920 --> 18:49.820
It's Gracie's dads.
Just let me do the talking.

18:49.920 --> 18:51.340
(MURMURS)

18:51.440 --> 18:54.220
-SANTI: Hey.
-Hi.

18:54.320 --> 18:57.620
I'm Austin. This is Karl.
We're Gracie's dads.

18:57.720 --> 18:59.460
I know.

18:59.560 --> 19:02.080
-I'm Bernardita.
-Santi.

19:03.880 --> 19:06.820
(CLEARS THROAT)
This is kind of delicate.

19:06.920 --> 19:09.100
Yeah, look, I've been planning
to talk to you guys.

19:09.200 --> 19:11.660
About how our kids
attacked each other?

19:11.760 --> 19:13.760
This isn't about that.

19:15.160 --> 19:17.100
Something happened
with Gracie today

19:17.200 --> 19:19.500
which I am not allowed
to talk about.

19:19.600 --> 19:23.460
It's a "cross my heart
and hope to die" situation.

19:23.560 --> 19:25.680
-You understand?
-Uh-huh.

19:26.680 --> 19:28.940
What I can say is

19:29.040 --> 19:32.100
our daughter really needed
a friend today

19:32.200 --> 19:33.860
and your Jacinda stepped up.

19:33.960 --> 19:37.440
Gracie's so grateful.
And so are we.

19:38.440 --> 19:40.720
I feel like we might have
misjudged their friendship.

19:41.720 --> 19:42.860
Oh.

19:42.960 --> 19:46.220
Maybe we could organise
a play date for them?

19:46.320 --> 19:48.620
J could come to our place
one weekend?

19:48.720 --> 19:50.880
Or Gracie can come to our place.

19:52.200 --> 19:53.580
Yeah, absolutely.

19:53.680 --> 19:55.340
SANTI: Awesome.

19:55.440 --> 19:58.440
(UPBEAT MUSIC)

20:23.560 --> 20:25.560
(MUSIC ENDS)

20:26.320 --> 20:28.320
(INSECTS CHIRP)

20:33.680 --> 20:37.580
Should we, um...
Want to eat on the couch?

20:37.680 --> 20:39.680
OLY AND BOWIE: Yep.

20:47.280 --> 20:49.280
Listen.

20:51.080 --> 20:53.080
-I just want to say that...
-No need.

20:55.080 --> 20:58.340
Uh, look, I don't want to talk
about it either. And we won't.

20:58.440 --> 20:59.820
Ever again.

20:59.920 --> 21:02.500
But, um,
I do want you both to know

21:02.600 --> 21:05.380
that this thing with Edith,

21:05.480 --> 21:07.480
it...it's a good thing.

21:08.960 --> 21:11.060
You know, obviously I didn't,

21:11.160 --> 21:14.540
um, want you to find out
the way you did.

21:14.640 --> 21:18.100
Um, but, to be honest,
I don't know what's happening.

21:18.200 --> 21:21.220
But what I do know
is that I'm...

21:21.320 --> 21:23.320
I don't know.

21:24.280 --> 21:26.280
..happy.

21:29.360 --> 21:32.200
So, um, that's it. The end.

21:33.200 --> 21:36.000
We are happy too.

21:37.400 --> 21:39.740
Happiness
is one of the many feelings

21:39.840 --> 21:42.500
that we're grappling with
right now.

21:42.600 --> 21:45.220
You don't have to
justify yourself to us.

21:45.320 --> 21:47.700
You've opened the cage door,

21:47.800 --> 21:49.220
you're flapping your wings,

21:49.320 --> 21:51.620
you've tapped into
the divine feminine.

21:51.720 --> 21:54.200
How is that not awesome?

21:55.840 --> 21:57.840
Yeah, it is awesome.

22:01.000 --> 22:02.540
How's your dad?

22:02.640 --> 22:04.640
Uh...

22:05.600 --> 22:06.980
He's not great.

22:07.080 --> 22:11.440
Yeah, you'd think he'd be
used to your sexcapades by now.

22:12.560 --> 22:14.560
It's the second time?

22:15.080 --> 22:16.620
Mmm, third.

22:16.720 --> 22:18.720
-Third?
-Yep.

22:21.920 --> 22:25.800
OK, I've decided that I want to
be a part of this baby's life.

22:26.920 --> 22:29.420
And I also want to have a say
in its future.

22:29.520 --> 22:33.500
We can fight as much as we like,

22:33.600 --> 22:36.260
but we all know that the baby
is the most important thing.

22:36.360 --> 22:38.580
I think the best way forward

22:38.680 --> 22:41.100
is if we all see a lawyer,

22:41.200 --> 22:43.920
set some ground rules
that we can all agree on.

22:46.600 --> 22:48.100
Are these gluten-free?

22:48.200 --> 22:50.200
Of course.

22:51.280 --> 22:53.280
OK.

22:54.720 --> 22:56.720
OK.

22:57.560 --> 22:59.560
OK.

23:04.720 --> 23:06.720
(GATE SQUEAKS)

23:08.400 --> 23:10.380
Hi.

23:10.480 --> 23:13.060
I've thought about it
and I don't care.

23:13.160 --> 23:15.100
-Huh?
-(LOUDLY) I don't care!

23:15.200 --> 23:18.460
Love is rare
and we're all gonna die,

23:18.560 --> 23:21.560
so I want you to know
I'm happy for you both.

23:22.800 --> 23:25.200
Do you mean that? Because
you're kind of screaming.

23:27.040 --> 23:28.940
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

23:29.040 --> 23:30.580
Doesn't matter what I think.

23:30.680 --> 23:32.580
It doesn't matter
what Oly and Bowie thinks.

23:32.680 --> 23:34.060
If Angie is what you want,

23:34.160 --> 23:36.820
then you should go for it 100%.

23:36.920 --> 23:38.540
Fuck the consequences.

23:38.640 --> 23:41.220
OK. Wow! Well, um, thanks.

23:41.320 --> 23:43.320
See ya!

23:43.680 --> 23:45.300
Dom.

23:45.400 --> 23:47.400
(DOM SIGHS)

23:48.480 --> 23:50.260
Really?

23:50.360 --> 23:52.360
Yeah!

23:59.080 --> 24:01.140
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

24:01.240 --> 24:04.380
-(GASPS) Hey.
-Hey.

24:04.480 --> 24:06.480
Come in.

24:07.520 --> 24:09.520
I can't.

24:11.840 --> 24:13.840
OK.

24:14.840 --> 24:16.840
(SIGHS)

24:17.400 --> 24:19.400
God, I love you, Angie.

24:21.120 --> 24:22.820
I love you too.

24:22.920 --> 24:25.420
I've always loved you.
You know that, yeah?

24:25.520 --> 24:27.540
Yeah.

24:27.640 --> 24:30.580
That's...that's great, isn't it?

24:30.680 --> 24:31.980
What's happened?

24:32.080 --> 24:34.480
Um, nothing, but, um...

24:36.920 --> 24:39.280
..I don't think I can do this.

24:41.760 --> 24:43.780
Of course you can.

24:43.880 --> 24:45.260
I can't. I can't.

24:45.360 --> 24:48.800
I want to - very much -
but, um...I can't.

24:49.960 --> 24:52.460
(SIGHS) I, um...

24:52.560 --> 24:55.660
I can't risk everything
for this.

24:55.760 --> 24:57.760
I...

24:58.160 --> 24:59.580
There's Dom,
there's...there's Oly,

24:59.680 --> 25:01.060
Bowie...

25:01.160 --> 25:04.540
Edith, you're catastrophising.
This has just started.

25:04.640 --> 25:07.700
Not for me, you know?
Not for me.

25:07.800 --> 25:09.580
This has been going on
a very long time.

25:09.680 --> 25:13.220
Stop. Just breathe. Come in.

25:13.320 --> 25:15.560
And come on, come in,
we'll talk about it.

25:16.800 --> 25:19.860
Sweetie, I can't come in.
I'll kiss you.

25:19.960 --> 25:21.960
I want you to kiss me.

25:22.800 --> 25:24.800
Please don't make this hard.

25:25.760 --> 25:26.780
What? That's it?

25:26.880 --> 25:30.400
Yeah, that's it.
I'm...I'm sorry.

25:31.400 --> 25:32.900
I'm sorry, Angie.

25:33.000 --> 25:35.000
